ticipated that this research would provide helpful information to the public and assist researchers in the future based on the findings of this topic area. Data was collected using a Google Form and distributed via social media like WhatsApp. The targeted respondents are between 15 and 34 years old and are located in the Klang Valley area. Statistical Package for the Social Sciences (SPSS) version 27 system was used to determine digital advertising characteristics electronically. T-test and ANOVA tests were applied in this study to examine the demographic factors that affect the relationship between the variables, as different backgrounds influence the perspectives and behaviours of the users. The findings show that the independent variable, the influence of Facebook, has a strong correlation with the dependent variable, the effectiveness of digital advertising among Malaysian youth in Klang Valley (r= 0.770). Socio-demographic factors such as age and educational level had an effect on the relationship between the variables. The effectiveness of digital advertising is influenced by the number of likes, comments, and shares by Facebook users. © Universiti Telekom Sdn Bhd. This article is licensed under.","digital advertising; Facebook; Klang Valley; Malaysian youth; socio-demographic","","","","T.H. Lin; Faculty of Applied Communication, Multimedia University, Cyberjaya, Selangor, Malaysia; email: huilin010910@gmail.com","","Multimedia University Press (MMU Press)","","","","","English","J. commun. lang. cult.","Article","Final","All Open Access; Gold Open Access","Scopus","2-s2.0-105019530700"
