onsored spending on Meta in the 2022 general election period made appeals for donations, with significant variation across campaigns. The Meta and Google ad libraries are invaluable sources of data for measuring the digital strategies of campaigns, but the declines from 2020, particularly on Meta, suggest candidates are likely pursuing diverse digital investments across platforms, some with no transparency or capacity to track spending and content. © 2023 the author(s), published by De Gruyter, Berlin/Boston.","abortion; digital ads; elections; Facebook; Google; Instagram; negative campaigns; YouTube","","","","E.F. Fowler; Wesleyan University, Middletown, United States; email: efowler@wesleyan.edu","","De Gruyter Open Ltd","15408884; 21946183","","","","English","Forum","Article","Final","All Open Access; Hybrid Gold Open Access","Scopus","2-s2.0-85159303948"
